WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.467 --> 00:00:04.834
♪♪

00:00:04.834 --> 00:00:06.667
Narrator:
WITH SO MUCH ON THEIR PLATES,

00:00:06.667 --> 00:00:11.000
BUSY PEOPLE RELY ON SHORTCUTS
TO HELP PREPARE MEALS.

00:00:11.000 --> 00:00:13.033
NOWADAYS,
YOU CAN STOCK YOUR PANTRY

00:00:13.033 --> 00:00:15.200
WITH CANS OF PRECOOKED MEAT

00:00:15.200 --> 00:00:18.167
SO THERE'S ALWAYS SOMETHING
ON HAND TO USE IN SANDWICHES,

00:00:18.167 --> 00:00:21.801
STEWS, STIR-FRIES,
AND OTHER TASTY DISHES.

00:00:24.634 --> 00:00:27.834
THIS CANNED MEAT IS
METICULOUSLY HAND-PRODUCED

00:00:27.834 --> 00:00:31.234
BY A CRAFT CANNERY
AND MADE IN SMALL BATCHES.

00:00:31.234 --> 00:00:33.834
♪♪

00:00:33.834 --> 00:00:37.400
IT CONTAINS NO ARTIFICIAL
INGREDIENTS OR PRESERVATIVES,

00:00:37.400 --> 00:00:39.734
JUST MEAT AND SEA SALT.

00:00:39.734 --> 00:00:42.501
WHEN A SHIPMENT OF MEAT
ARRIVES AT THE CANNERY,

00:00:42.501 --> 00:00:45.300
THE QUALITY CONTROL MANAGER
RECORDS ITS LOT CODE

00:00:45.300 --> 00:00:47.968
FOR TRACKING PURPOSES.

00:00:47.968 --> 00:00:49.667
AS A FOOD-SAFETY PRECAUTION,

00:00:49.667 --> 00:00:52.033
HE CONFIRMS THE TEMPERATURE
OF THE MEAT,

00:00:52.033 --> 00:00:57.033
WHICH MUST COME IN BETWEEN
ZERO TO 39° FAHRENHEIT.

00:00:57.033 --> 00:00:59.934
A SKILLED BUTCHER
THEN INSPECTS THE MEAT

00:00:59.934 --> 00:01:02.100
AND TRIMS OFF THE EXCESS FAT.

00:01:02.100 --> 00:01:07.767
♪♪

00:01:07.767 --> 00:01:09.167
IF IT'S A LARGE PIECE,

00:01:09.167 --> 00:01:11.767
THE BUTCHER SLICES IT
INTO SMALLER PIECES

00:01:11.767 --> 00:01:14.167
SO THAT IT CAN PASS THROUGH
THE DICING MACHINE.

00:01:14.167 --> 00:01:17.234
♪♪

00:01:17.234 --> 00:01:20.367
THE DICER CUTS THE MEAT
INTO ONE-INCH CUBES.

00:01:20.367 --> 00:01:26.868
♪♪

00:01:26.868 --> 00:01:28.267
AT THE FILLING STATION,

00:01:28.267 --> 00:01:32.200
ALUMINUM CANS CIRCULATE
AROUND A ROTATING TABLE.

00:01:32.200 --> 00:01:36.234
AS ONE WORKER SHOVELS CUBED MEAT
ONTO THE CENTER OF THE TABLE,

00:01:36.234 --> 00:01:38.534
OTHERS MANUALLY FILL CANS

00:01:38.534 --> 00:01:42.200
WHILE SIMULTANEOUSLY PERFORMING
A QUALITY INSPECTION.

00:01:42.200 --> 00:01:44.300
WORKERS WILL DISCARD ANY CUBES

00:01:44.300 --> 00:01:48.901
THAT ARE DISCOLORED
OR TOO FATTY.

00:01:48.901 --> 00:01:52.367
NEXT, TECHNICIANS PLACE
A SINGLE CUBE OF SEA SALT

00:01:52.367 --> 00:01:54.467
IN EACH CAN FILLED WITH MEAT.

00:01:54.467 --> 00:01:57.834
♪♪

00:01:57.834 --> 00:02:00.133
THIS IS THE ONLY
ADDED INGREDIENT.

00:02:00.133 --> 00:02:08.801
♪♪

00:02:08.801 --> 00:02:12.400
AT THE NEXT STATION, WORKERS
WEIGH EACH CAN INDIVIDUALLY

00:02:12.400 --> 00:02:16.634
AND EITHER ADD OR REMOVE MEAT
TO REACH THE REQUIRED WEIGHT.

00:02:16.634 --> 00:02:19.667
♪♪

00:02:19.667 --> 00:02:22.501
THE FILLED CANS NOW TRAVEL
ON A CONVEYER BELT

00:02:22.501 --> 00:02:25.234
TO THE COOK ROOM.

00:02:25.234 --> 00:02:27.167
THERE, THEY ENTER
THE PRE-HEATER,

00:02:27.167 --> 00:02:30.968
WHICH BLASTS THEM WITH STEAM
FOR 20 SECONDS.

00:02:30.968 --> 00:02:34.267
THIS EXPELS AIR THAT'S TRAPPED
BETWEEN THE CUBES OF MEAT.

00:02:34.267 --> 00:02:36.534
♪♪

00:02:36.534 --> 00:02:39.834
NEXT, THE CANS MOVE
INTO THE CLOSING MACHINE.

00:02:39.834 --> 00:02:41.567
THE MACHINE COMPRESSES THE MEAT

00:02:41.567 --> 00:02:44.901
TO PROVIDE SUFFICIENT CLEARANCE
AT THE TOP OF THE CAN.

00:02:44.901 --> 00:02:48.167
THIS HEAD SPACE
CREATES A VACUUM ON THE CAN

00:02:48.167 --> 00:02:49.968
TO DRAW OUT THE REMAINING AIR.

00:02:49.968 --> 00:02:53.501
♪♪

00:02:53.501 --> 00:02:55.801
THEN, A DEVICE ATTACHES THE LID

00:02:55.801 --> 00:02:59.100
BY A PROCESS KNOWN
AS DOUBLE SEAMING.

00:02:59.100 --> 00:03:03.100
THE PROCESS ROLLS THE EDGES
OF THE LID AND CAN TOGETHER,

00:03:03.100 --> 00:03:05.834
FORMING A RIM THAT PROVIDES
AN AIRTIGHT SEAL.

00:03:05.834 --> 00:03:08.968
♪♪

00:03:08.968 --> 00:03:11.734
IT'S TIME TO GET COOKING.

00:03:11.734 --> 00:03:13.367
A WORKER LOWERS THE CANS

00:03:13.367 --> 00:03:15.634
INTO A COMMERCIAL-SIZED
PRESSURE COOKER.

00:03:15.634 --> 00:03:19.367
♪♪

00:03:19.367 --> 00:03:21.167
COOKING UNDER STEAM PRESSURE

00:03:21.167 --> 00:03:23.834
PRODUCES THE TENDERIZING
EFFECTS OF SLOW COOKING

00:03:23.834 --> 00:03:25.701
IN A FRACTION OF THE TIME.

00:03:25.701 --> 00:03:28.634
♪♪

00:03:28.634 --> 00:03:31.133
THE MEAT COOKS
IN ITS OWN JUICES.

00:03:31.133 --> 00:03:32.501
THE COOKING TEMPERATURE VARIES,

00:03:32.501 --> 00:03:35.534
DEPENDING ON THE TYPE OF MEAT
AND THE CAN SIZE.

00:03:35.534 --> 00:03:39.434
♪♪

00:03:39.434 --> 00:03:43.000
WHEN THE MEAT IS READY,
THE TECHNICIAN REMOVES THE CANS

00:03:43.000 --> 00:03:45.234
AND SETS THEM ASIDE
FOR ABOUT AN HOUR

00:03:45.234 --> 00:03:46.601
TO COOL AND DRY.

00:03:46.601 --> 00:03:50.400
♪♪

00:03:50.400 --> 00:03:53.033
THE CANS ARE THEN MOVED
TO THE PACKAGING AREA.

00:03:53.033 --> 00:03:55.567
♪♪

00:03:55.567 --> 00:03:58.000
AS A WORKER LOADS
THE LABELING MACHINE,

00:03:58.000 --> 00:04:01.868
HE INSPECTS EACH CAN
FOR DENTS OR DAMAGED SEALS.

00:04:01.868 --> 00:04:04.067
♪♪

00:04:04.067 --> 00:04:07.567
ONE BY ONE, THE CANS ROLL
OVER A GLUE APPLICATOR,

00:04:07.567 --> 00:04:09.434
THEN A STACK OF LABELS,

00:04:09.434 --> 00:04:12.767
WRAPPING THEMSELVES
IN THE TOP SEAL.

00:04:12.767 --> 00:04:16.334
AT THE SAME TIME, THE MACHINE
COUNTS THE NUMBER OF CANS.

00:04:16.334 --> 00:04:21.400
♪♪

00:04:21.400 --> 00:04:23.601
AFTER ROLLING OFF
THE LABELING MACHINE,

00:04:23.601 --> 00:04:26.067
THE CANS PASS
THROUGH AN INK-JET PRINTER

00:04:26.067 --> 00:04:28.534
WHICH APPLIES
THE BEST-USED-BY DATE.

00:04:28.534 --> 00:04:32.868
♪♪

00:04:32.868 --> 00:04:35.501
THAT DATE IS NEXT
TO THE LOT CODE,

00:04:35.501 --> 00:04:39.734
WHICH THE CLOSING MACHINE
PRINTED WHILE ATTACHING THE LID.

00:04:39.734 --> 00:04:42.667
THIS CAN OF MEAT
HAS A FIVE-YEAR SHELF LIFE,

00:04:42.667 --> 00:04:45.000
DUE TO TWO CRUCIAL FACTORS:

00:04:45.000 --> 00:04:49.133
IT IS COOKED PROPERLY
AND THE CAN'S SEAL IS AIRTIGHT.

00:04:49.133 --> 00:04:53.934
♪♪

